of the grain from every field

48:17.440 --> 48:19.200
and store it under guard.

48:19.280 --> 48:23.000
Then, during the famine,
give it back to the people.

48:23.080 --> 48:25.960
Potiphar, you trust this man?

48:27.560 --> 48:29.520
With my life, Excellency.

48:31.320 --> 48:34.280
(Crowd cheering)

48:37.040 --> 48:38.800
(Crowd silences)

48:38.880 --> 48:42.200
Through this man,
I have seen the future of Egypt.

48:44.240 --> 48:47.840
And through his deeds,
we shall prosper.

48:47.920 --> 48:49.800
(Crowd cheers)

48:52.160 --> 48:55.240
I am giving him power over all Egypt.

48:55.320 --> 48:57.920
Only Pharaoh will be greater.

48:58.000 --> 49:01.440
You shall call him Tzafenat Paneah.

49:01.520 --> 49:04.480
The God speaks and He lives.

49:06.200 --> 49:09.840
