54:27.920 --> 54:30.800
- Thank you!
- Bye!

54:30.920 --> 54:33.360
(Cries out)

54:34.960 --> 54:39.160
- Here you go.
- (Potiphar) Who's next?

54:39.240 --> 54:41.720
We are, my lord.

54:42.960 --> 54:46.040
- You are not Egyptian.
- No, sir.

54:46.120 --> 54:49.280
My brothers and I
have travelled far, from Canaan.

54:55.920 --> 54:59.040
- Joseph, what's wrong?
- Nothing.

54:59.120 --> 55:01.560
Look at you. You're shaking.

55:01.640 --> 55:03.920
I-it must be the sun. I'll be fine.

55:04.000 --> 55:06.280
(Judah) Our families are hungry.

55:06.400 --> 55:09.240
You haven't contributed
to our supply.

55:09.320 --> 55:12.760
We don't ask for charity.
We'll pay you with silver.

55:16.800 --> 55:18.800
(Potiphar) How many are there?

55:18.880 --> 55:23.360
12. 10 here and at home we have
our father and youngest brother.

55:23.440 --> 55:25.480
- (Gasps)
- (Potiphar) Give them...

55:25.560 --> 55:27.560
(Joseph) Nothing!

55:27.640 --> 55:32.160
10 foreigners asking
for grain, no ties to Egypt.

55:32.240 --> 55:35.920
Are you thieves, hoping to see
where we store our grain?

55:36.000 --> 55:39.760
I don't know what you are,
but I don't believe your story.

55:39.840 --> 55:42.880
Your Excellency,
everything we say is true.

55:42.960 --> 55:45.960
Prove it!
Produce this youngest brother.

55:46.040 --> 55:49.520
- But what would that prove?
- That you're not lying.

55:49.600 --> 55:52.400
If it's the truth,
I'll let you buy grain.

55:52.480 --> 55:56.000
Till then, arrest this one!

55:56.080 --> 55:59.080
- (Gasps)
- Until you produce this brother.

55:59.160 --> 56:01.360
- Take him.
- (Grunting)

56:01.440 --> 56:03.360
