bloom and forgive... #

58:52.320 --> 58:53.920
Tzafenat Paneah...

58:54.000 --> 58:57.160
The family of Canaanites...
They've returned.

58:57.240 --> 58:58.880
Thank you.

58:59.560 --> 59:03.080
Maybe they've suffered
these last 20 years as well.

59:03.160 --> 59:05.200
- Maybe they've changed.
- No.

59:05.280 --> 59:07.280
I don't think so.

59:07.360 --> 59:09.600
(Door closes)

59:10.720 --> 59:13.800
(Murmuring)

59:13.880 --> 59:16.120
Don't speak unless you're spoken to.

59:19.280 --> 59:22.040
Don't worry. It'll be all right.

59:33.520 --> 59:35.520
Welcome.

59:35.600 --> 59:40.320
- You've done what I've asked?
- Our brother, Benjamin.

59:51.040 --> 59:55.040
You kept your word.
Bring out the other brother.

59:55.120 --> 01:00:00.480
So, Benjamin,
tell me of your mother and father.

01:00:00.560 --> 01:00:04.120
My mother is no longer alive.

01:00:04.200 --> 01:00:08.040
Oh. I- I'm sorry.

01:00:09.320 --> 01:00:11.360
And your father?

01:00:11.440 --> 01:00:14.520
- He's worried I'm here.
- Why is that?

01:00:14.600 --> 01:00:19.920
- I'm a long way from home.
- Oh? Doesn't he trust your brothers?

01:00:20.000 --> 01:00:22.480
He likes me to stay close by.

01:00:22.560 --> 01:00:25.320
Really? Why is that?

01:00:26.880 --> 01:00:30.000
A long time ago,
h-he lost his youngest son.

01:00:30.080 --> 01:00:33.360
Well, I'm sorry to hear that.
How did that happen?

01:00:33.440 --> 01:00:36.000
- He was killed.
- Killed? How?

01:00:36.080 --> 01:00:37.880
By wolves.

01:00:37.960 --> 01:00:41.840
- Wolves?
- Yes.

01:00:41.920 --> 01:00:44.560
It broke my father's heart.

01:00:44.640 --> 01:00:49.800
Well, it must have been very hard
on your brothers too.

01:00:49.880 --> 01:00:53.040
- They never speak of it.
- Don't they?

01:00:53.160 --> 01:00:56.160
- Benjamin!
- (Brothers) Simeon!

01:00:56.240 --> 01:00:59.480
- I was beginning to worry.
- (All murmuring)

01:00:59.560 --> 01:01:03.920
You must be hungry
after your journey. Come.

01:01:04.000 --> 01:01:06.840
You'll be my guests.

01:01:06.920 --> 01:01:09.640
(Traditional music)

01:01:32.240 --> 01:01:34.200
- A toast...
- (Music stops)

01:01:35.400 --> 01:01:36.960
to brothers.

01:01:37.040 --> 01:01:39.760
(All) To brothers!

01:01:39.840 --> 01:01:41.640
(Music resumes)

01:01:58.200 --> 01:02:00.560
(Brothers arguing and protesting)

01:02:02.720 --> 01:02:06.160
Stop this. You have no right.
We've done nothing wrong.

01:02:09.480 --> 01:02:13.640
What's going on?
Why have they been arrested?

01:02:13.720 --> 01:02:16.640
- Joseph, what are you doing?
- You'll see.

01:02:17.520 --> 01:02:20.440
Get back in place. Get back in...

01:02:20.560 --> 01:02:24.680
I give you food.
I take you into my home.

01:02:24.760 --> 01:02:28.560
And this is how you repay me,
by stealing?

01:02:28.640 --> 01:02:30.520
We wouldn't steal from you!

01:02:30.600 --> 01:02:33.240
- And now you insult me by lying.
- What?

01:02:33.320 --> 01:02:36.320
One of you has stolen from me.

01:02:44.920 --> 01:02:47.000
Benjamin.

01:02:53.680 --> 01:02:56.640
- (Murmuring) No...
- The favoured one.

01:02:56.720 --> 01:02:58.480
- I didn't!
- Arrest him.

01:02:58.560 --> 01:03:01.360
For this you will be punished.

01:03:01.440 --> 01:03:04.680
- Someone put it there!
- Stop! Take me instead.

01:03:04.800 --> 01:03:07.680
- No, take me.
- Take me!

01:03:07.760 --> 01:03:10.680
- (All) Take me!
- Take any of us, your grace,

01:03:10.760 --> 01:03:13.120
